4. EPFO Mystery Investigation

Target stakeholders: Compliance officers, enforcement officers, employers, auditors
Game format: Investigation and detective game

The player investigates fictional establishments for possible EPF Act violations. They receive clues from payroll records, attendance, contractor bills, balance sheets, employee complaints, and ECR filings.

The goal is to identify issues such as non-enrolment, under-reporting of wages, splitting of wages, contractor employee non-compliance, delayed remittance, or bogus compliance.

Learning outcomes:

Enforcement staff learn inspection logic. Employers learn what not to do.

Example mission:

“ABC Manufacturing shows 18 employees in ECR but 42 workers in attendance records. Investigate.”

Player checks:

Payroll register
Contractor agreement
Wage sheet
Bank salary statement
ECR data
Employee statements

Gamification:

Evidence strength meter, investigation quality score, “fair assessment” badge, appeal-risk indicator.
